Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.63,0:00:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, class...\NTell me what the decision
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.57,0:00:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,in the 1968 Stuttgart case\Nwas based upon.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.18,0:00:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, now, what is this silence?\NIs this a Zen temple in the Orient?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.28,0:00:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Eimer... I would like to\Nhear your answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.79,0:00:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.82,0:00:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Well... uh... That is...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.93,0:00:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone! Is there anyone\Nwho will break this silence?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.47,0:00:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the chronic latecomer is here at last.\NYou're 13 minutes late...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.54,0:00:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Seems your part-time pizza delivery job\Nwas awfully busy today.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.28,0:01:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry... Professor... Kronecker...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.69,0:01:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, then, let me ask you a question\Nbefore you sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.46,0:01:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have enough strength\Nto tell me what the basis was
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.06,0:01:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,for the decision in the Stuttgart case?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.93,0:01:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Uh... yes. Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.27,0:01:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The accused claimed that\Nthe kidnapping was a sham
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.07,0:01:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and that the victim's death\Nhad been due to an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.27,0:01:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,After an investigation\Nof the crime scene
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.88,0:01:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,it was found that the victim's death\Nhad indeed been accidental.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.45,0:01:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, based on the fact that the intent\Nto kill must be proven in a murder
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.52,0:01:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe that a sentence\Nof 15 years was handed down.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.19,0:01:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Very good.\NSit down, Nina Fortner.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.53,0:01:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Professor!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.63,0:03:23.18,Titles1,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,500)\an8}Heidelberg,\N(Germany)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.46,0:03:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You saved us, Nina.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.80,0:03:28.77,Monster-Title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(750,750)\pos(360,340)}The Girl of Heidelberg
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.03,0:03:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If no one had been able to\Ngive him the answer,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.23,0:03:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Kronecker would have probably\Ndemanded 50-page reports.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.80,0:03:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,50 pages, if we were lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.87,0:03:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to treat Nina, to whom we're\Ngreatly indebted, to something to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.17,0:03:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You can come, can't you Nina?\NJust the two of us...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.28,0:03:44.20,Names2,,0,0,15,,{\fad(300,0)}Nina Fortner
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.34,0:03:44.11,Default,,0,0,90,,I'm sorry, Peter.\NI have a club meeting today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.01,0:03:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,See you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.52,0:03:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,She turned you down again...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.72,0:03:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Peter, how many times was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.49,0:03:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up! I'd like to see if there's anyone\Nwho can get Nina to agree to a date.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.44,0:04:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.91,0:04:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no! If I'm late with my deliveries,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.41,0:04:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to get it\Nfrom the manager again!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.60,0:04:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm home!\NBoy, am I hungry!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.83,0:04:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my, the neighbors\Ncan probably hear you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.20,0:04:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a young lady now.\NIt's not becoming.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.07,0:04:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Go and wash your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.10,0:04:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.44,0:04:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Mom, did you\Ncolor your hair?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.68,0:04:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks good, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.11,0:04:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly! You shouldn't be dying\Nyour hair so bright, at your age!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.35,0:04:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You're wrong, Dad.\NShe looks lovely.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.42,0:04:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,She's not going to\Na masquerade party, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.79,0:05:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't it be wonderful\Nfor Mom to be young forever?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.99,0:05:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.09,0:05:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes... Speaking of masquerades...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.43,0:05:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw some kids in costumes today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.23,0:05:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes...\NIt's the St. Hadrian Costume Parade.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.94,0:05:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish I had dressed up like that\Nwhen I was little. They were so cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.54,0:05:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Oh... you did dress up\Nin a costume.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.28,0:05:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, dear?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.98,0:05:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Oh... that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.59,0:05:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.75,0:05:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see... It's around here...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.22,0:05:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, here it is!\NHere, look at this!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.20,0:05:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.50,0:05:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You were so excited\Nand made such a fuss.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.77,0:05:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, dear?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.94,0:05:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Oh, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.75,0:06:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,A costume parade?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.46,0:06:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Distant spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.70,0:06:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I forlornly wait for a spring\Nthat will never come... Hannah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.30,0:06:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Hannah... Will you hurry\Nand get over your broken heart?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.91,0:06:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.64,0:06:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me send you\Nthe world's most beautiful flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.45,0:06:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I was born to blanket you in flowers...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.22,0:06:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow... I wonder who sent this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.22,0:06:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Aha!\NI'm very impressed, Peter!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.86,0:06:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,How have you been, Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.63,0:06:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, well, I've been very well,\Nthankfully, Dr. Gaitel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.37,0:06:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.93,0:06:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, I could tell by the look\Non your face when you entered
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.64,0:06:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,this counseling room\Nthat your were doing well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.04,0:07:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And do you no longer\Nhave that dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.84,0:07:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Of that monster appearing\Nout of the darkness...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.95,0:07:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! I've been sleeping so well,\NI have no time to dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.19,0:07:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder why I was plagued by\Nsuch a dream night after night.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.12,0:07:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's common for people to become\Ninsecure during their student years.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.79,0:07:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Dreams of the future become\Nconfused with other insecurities,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.60,0:07:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and you lose sight of who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.80,0:07:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But what you are is something\Nyou can spend your whole life
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.60,0:07:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to learn, and never discover.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.24,0:07:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,All you can do now is be prepared\Nto spend your whole life searching,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.28,0:07:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and do only what you can do\Ntoward your future.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.38,0:07:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I will do my best.\NI want to become a public prosecutor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.55,0:07:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's good. All right, I think we can\Nend our counseling session for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.49,0:07:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.93,0:07:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina Fortner... Such a cheerful girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.93,0:08:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But I can't help but feel\Nthat her cheerfulness
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.10,0:08:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,is a reaction to something\Nshe's running away from.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.21,0:08:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Some... vast... darkness...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.11,0:08:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.15,0:08:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't say that.\NDon't act so innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.68,0:08:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What in the world\Nare you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.92,0:08:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,"I was born to\Nblanket you in flowers..."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.56,0:08:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I never thought you had\Nthe makings of a poet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.19,0:08:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know anything about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.90,0:08:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't be able to come up with words\Nlike those even if I stood on my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.03,0:08:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Then, who was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.80,0:08:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I've given my email address\Nto only my friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.14,0:08:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.64,0:08:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn. All I know is that\NI have another rival in love!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.18,0:08:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Who in the world could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.25,0:08:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This bizarre murder\Nthat took place in Munich...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.73,0:09:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The perpetrator,\Nafter shooting the parents to death,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.36,0:09:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,strangled the two children with a rope.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.37,0:09:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I'd like you to explain the ruling\Nof the judge from the court records...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.14,0:09:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina Fortner.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.74,0:09:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.14,0:09:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you not understand the question?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.75,0:09:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,N-No... uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.32,0:09:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The trial was focused on\Nthe cold-blooded murder
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.19,0:09:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of a whole family...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.76,0:09:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,- Huh?\N- The evidence...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.89,0:09:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The evidence...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.26,0:09:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? There are times\Nyou can't answer either, Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.54,0:09:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.38,0:09:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.75,0:09:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.25,0:09:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you all right?\NYou want to go to the infirmary?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.95,0:10:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I'm all right.\NI just felt a little ill...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.76,0:10:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,After listening to the professor's story...\Nsuddenly...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.56,0:10:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? You mean that bizarre\Nmassacre of that family?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.93,0:10:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.54,0:10:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.77,0:10:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you were awfully brave,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.01,0:10:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're more sensitive\Nthan I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.64,0:10:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you see a horror movie\Nthat terrified you as a child?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.95,0:10:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I know! I'll bet that counselor,\NDr. Gaitel, would probably say...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.18,0:10:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,"If you look back on\Nwhy this happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.22,0:10:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll find it was nothing significant.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.09,0:10:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, why don't you think back\Non your childhood..."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.42,0:10:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.33,0:10:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.76,0:10:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember anything\Nbefore the age of ten...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.65,0:11:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,My memories...\NMy childhood memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.16,0:11:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.57,0:11:21.07,Titles1,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Köln,\N(Germany)
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.50,0:11:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.57,0:11:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They were a very nice couple...\NTo think they were killed like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.44,0:11:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Children?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.01,0:11:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, now that you mention it,\Nthey had a son.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.82,0:11:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,His name was Michael, I think.\NThey lived together about two years.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.42,0:11:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,A boy? Was there a boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.29,0:11:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, there was.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.89,0:11:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Wasn't his name Michael?\NHe was around fourteen.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.53,0:11:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Michael, you say?\NI seem to remember him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.40,0:11:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Are you the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.74,0:12:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Michael Reichmann.\NHe was a student in my class.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.98,0:12:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But he didn't leave\Nmuch of an impression.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.85,0:12:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm embarrassed to say this,\Nbut I don't remember him well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.92,0:12:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure if he had any friends.\NAnd, there are no records...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.72,0:12:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything burned\Nin a fire six years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.63,0:12:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There definitely was a boy\Nnamed Michael living here
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.60,0:12:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}in Cologne until six years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.57,0:12:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And... Michael's real name...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.37,0:12:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Johan... I've used that name before...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.35,0:12:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Who... are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.25,0:12:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But what's the use in knowing that?\NWhat's the use?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.26,0:12:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He is a serial-killer who is a twin...\NThat's all there is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.23,0:12:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What am I doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.30,0:13:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A twin! What about his sister?\NWhere did his twin sister go?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.01,0:13:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,"I will come for you soon..."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.88,0:13:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.18,0:13:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll come for me soon?\NWhat does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.00,0:13:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,A child? Yes, there was...\Nabout 7 or 8 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.90,0:13:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So Mr. and Mrs. Heinemann,\Nwho were killed, were fostering a boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.84,0:13:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What was he like?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.51,0:13:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What was he like?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.48,0:13:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.55,0:13:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And he only lived with them\Nabout a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.42,0:13:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember\Nanything about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.15,0:13:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't that boy have a sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.86,0:13:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It was only that boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.46,0:13:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, I just want to forget about\Nwhat happened to that couple.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.23,0:13:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I even thought about moving away\Nafter it happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.10,0:14:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I know about that boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.31,0:14:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on in. I was just about to\Nfix some tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.22,0:14:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.49,0:14:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh... yes. Thank you.\NUh... I...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.73,0:14:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.05,0:14:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Please have some tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.96,0:14:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.30,0:15:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a doctor, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.13,0:15:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That boy told me.\NYou're Dr. Tenma, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.44,0:15:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He's coming for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.24,0:15:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.48,0:15:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no idea.\NIt was an anonymous message.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.02,0:15:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You look so happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.85,0:15:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not thinking a prince\Non a white horse
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.32,0:15:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,will be coming for you, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.32,0:15:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you jealous?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.76,0:15:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,There you go,\Ndaydreaming again, Nina.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.80,0:15:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,"I was born to blanket you in flowers..."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.33,0:15:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There aren't any kids\Nwho talk like that today.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.04,0:15:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.64,0:15:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, listen. Haven't you noticed\Na strange boy in class recently?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.04,0:15:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Yes, I have!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.68,0:15:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The one who calmly sits in\Nthat "legendary seat"in Room 12,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.81,0:15:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,where you're bound to be called on\Nby the teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.82,0:15:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, he's never called on.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.22,0:15:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. And do you know,\Nhe stares at Nina all through class!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.16,0:15:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,- Huh?\N- He's the one!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.33,0:16:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.56,0:16:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You know!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.89,0:16:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Your prince on the white horse!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.77,0:16:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That boy was extremely grateful\Nto you, Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.21,0:16:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He said you were the one\Nwho saved him;
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.21,0:16:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you meant more to him than a parent.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.91,0:16:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What name did he go by?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.15,0:16:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Franz... But he said\Nit wasn't his real name.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.49,0:16:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,He trusted you enough\Nto tell you that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.66,0:16:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That Franz, who had shown up\Nout of the blue,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.70,0:16:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,was cared for by\NMr. and Mrs. Heinemann,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.47,0:16:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,who lived in the flat across the hall,\Nfor a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.14,0:16:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,No, actually, it was 14 months\Nfrom March 1987 to April 1988.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.25,0:16:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, one day, he suddenly vanished.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.82,0:17:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He was very bright.\NAnd he was well-mannered.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.26,0:17:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he used to\Ncome to this apartment?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.82,0:17:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day. I lived alone\Nso I always welcomed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.23,0:17:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He sat in that seat\Nand spent his time studying.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.13,0:17:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,In no time, he had mastered
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.00,0:17:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the English and French\Nthat I taught him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.54,0:17:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,By the time he disappeared,\Nhe was fluent in both.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.71,0:17:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That 12-year-old boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.55,0:17:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there anything else\Nyou remember about him?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.79,0:17:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He always listened closely\Nto my stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.49,0:17:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What stories do you think\Nhe was most interested in?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.63,0:17:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.00,0:17:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,War stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.10,0:17:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,War?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.67,0:17:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,During World War II,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.27,0:17:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I was on the crew of a U-boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.04,0:17:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,His favorite story\Nwas about the time
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.54,0:18:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,we were attacked by a destroyer\Nof the Allied Forces...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.15,0:18:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We were at a depth of 120 meters...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.35,0:18:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We were attacked by the enemy
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.78,0:18:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and although we had suffered\Na fatal blow, we kept going.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.79,0:18:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Inside that groaning ship,\Nwe all waited in terror.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.56,0:18:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We returned from that living hell\N38 hours later.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.10,0:18:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,An ordinary child would probably
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.04,0:18:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,look at this as\Nanother adventure story...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.71,0:18:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But that boy was different.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.61,0:18:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What he was\Nmost interested in was...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.48,0:18:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the terror.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.95,0:18:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Extreme terror.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.18,0:18:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the reaction of a person\Nstanding on the edge of death?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.19,0:18:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That was his only interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.76,0:18:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,He took pleasure in terror!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.73,0:18:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What sort of expression
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.07,0:18:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,did he have while\Nlistening to your stories?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.14,0:19:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably had a gleam in his eye,\Nand a smile on his face.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.34,0:19:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.91,0:19:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I am blind, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.18,0:19:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I know neither his real name,\Nnor what he looks like.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.19,0:19:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Earlier, you said that boy\Ntrusted me, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.96,0:19:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,He never trusts anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.23,0:19:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one person\Nhe's ever trusted... his sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.27,0:19:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I'm looking for that sister!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.71,0:19:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,He said he would go and collect her\Nwhen she turned twenty.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.08,0:19:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Go where?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.31,0:19:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,To Heidelberg.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.88,0:19:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,See you later!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.15,0:19:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Ride carefully on your scooter.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.32,0:19:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I will!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.62,0:19:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.02,0:19:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.70,0:19:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Good bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.94,0:20:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess it's time...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.41,0:20:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.48,0:20:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We decided, didn't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.14,0:20:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That we'd tell her on her 20th birthday\Nthat she's not our child.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.02,0:20:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, wait, I can't...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.03,0:20:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?\NYou wanted to meet him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.50,0:20:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We told him you'd wait for him here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.77,0:20:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't screw up,\Nwith your "prince on a white horse."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.64,0:20:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,See you later!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.54,0:20:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... Clara! Beata!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.58,0:20:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,How could they do this\Nbehind my back!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.79,0:20:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.99,0:20:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,He's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.57,0:21:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,H-How do you do...\NYou're Nina Fortner?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.44,0:21:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.31,0:21:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh... I'm Otto Hubermann...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.68,0:21:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, hello...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.80,0:21:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Who is he...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.53,0:21:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Who is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.47,0:21:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I've seen him... somewhere... before...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.58,0:22:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.67,0:22:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.80,0:22:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,- Nina!\N- Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.60,0:22:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina! What's wrong?\NAre you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.44,0:22:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,- Nina, wake up!\N- Nina! Nina!?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.14,0:22:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,- Nina, wake up!\N- Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.61,0:22:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hey, Nina!\N- Hey, Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.91,0:22:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina, are you all right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.90,0:23:53.53,Monster-Title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(1000,0)\pos(360,340)}The Missing
